cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper deals with a neural architecture for generating 2D or 3D shapes based on constructive solid geometry principles. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a recurrent neural network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of policy gradient techniques, which are commonly used in control and optimization problems, falling under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
